'''National Gurdwara''' is a [[Sikhism|Sikh]] [[gurdwara]] located in [[Washington, D.C.]]
Located on [[Massachusetts Avenue (Washington, D.C.)|Massachusetts Avenue]], the National Gurdwara is the first and only Sikh institution in the capital of the [[United States]]. It is located near the [[Washington National Cathedral|National Cathedral]], [[United States Naval Observatory|Naval Observatory]] and [[American University]]. The gurdwara officially opened in February 2006, and cost over 2 million US [[dollar]]s. Along with religious services, [[Punjabi language]] classes and [[kirtan]] classes are held.
==External links== *[http://sikhgurdwaradc.org/ National Gurdwara DC] *[https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/02/17/AR2006021702051.html Washington Post article]
